                    <h3 class="text-center text-theme-colored2">10 Tips to become a Top Ranker in CLAT</h3>
                    

<p>
We at Maansarovar have trained over 10,000 students till date and believe in a very realistic approach towards becoming a top ranker in the CLAT examination. Below we share exactly what you need to do to get into your dream law college.
</p>

                           <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/MIO9OUYvUlU?si=MmHDOXQh9fR7m8E5" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>

<p class="bold">There are 5 sections that are asked in the CLAT exam –</p>

<ol>
<li>Legal Reasoning</li>
<li>General Awareness</li>
<li>English Comprehension</li>
<li>Logical Reasoning</li>
<li>Quantitative Aptitude</li>
</ol>

<h4>These Are Ten Things That You Must Do</h4>

<div class="section">
<h4>1. Read Newspaper Everyday</h4>

<p>
Newspaper is the most important source for CLAT exam preparation. Four sections i.e. legal reasoning, general awareness, english comprehension and logical reasoning are directly influenced by newspaper reading. It also improves reading speed and comprehension.
</p>

<p class="bold">Approach at Maansarovar</p>
<p>
Current affairs are divided into general, political and legal current affairs. Even though exhaustive material is provided, students are encouraged to read newspapers regularly to maintain accountability.
</p>
</div>
<a href="10-tips-to-become-a-top-ranker-in-clat" class="btn btn btn-dark btn-theme-colored hvr-float-shadow mt-30 btn-xl">Read More</a>



